gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: This point data layer represents addresses for Buffalo County, Wisconsin in YE2016. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Buffalo_Addresses_YE2016.gdb.[Site address points represent the location of site or service delivery addresses assigned by local governments.]

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [Point feature class has been placed on the physical building rather than the location of physical sign (Fire number). Feature class was designed primarily for Enhanced 911 geocoding ability and basic analysis. Points have been placed according to orthophotography from multiple years, no GPS coordinates have been recorded at this time.]

gmd:supplementalInformation.gco:CharacterString: This data was submitted to the UW geospatial archive in 2017. Content may be considered current as of December 31, 2016. It was published to the UW geospatial archive as part of the Wisconsin Department of Administration Land Information Program annual collection of public data for the year 2017. Augmented original metadata with UW-Madison specific elements.
